The 2013 White House Easter Egg Roll will take place on April 1st and is focused on promoting health and wellness with the theme, "Be Healthy, Be Active, Be You!" The event will feature live music, sports courts, cooking stations, storytelling, and Easter egg rolling. Special guests include Kid President, Jordin Sparks, Austin Mahone, Coco Jones, Sesame Street, and The Wanted. The event will be broadcasted live on obamawhitehouse.archives.gov/eastereggroll. There will be various activities such as obstacle courses, yoga, dancing, playing sports with professional athletes, and the traditional egg roll. More than 30,000 people from all 50 states and the District of Columbia have received tickets to the event, which will run from 7:30 AM to 6:45 PM.